  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently asked questions",
    "q1": "How does animal registration work?",
    "a1": "You photograph the animal's muzzle, fill in details (breed, age, owner, insurance) and submit. The AI generates a biometric profile in seconds.",
    "q2": "What is verification and when is it needed?",
    "a2": "Verification matches a new photo against an existing registered profile. Used during insurance claims, animal sales, or ownership transfers.",
    "q3": "Is special equipment required?",
    "a3": "No. Any smartphone with a camera works. The system processes photos from 2 MP and above.",
    "q4": "How accurate is AI identification?",
    "a4": "Recognition accuracy in testing exceeds 95%. When confidence is low, the system requests additional photos.",
    "q5": "How is my data protected?",
    "a5": "Data is stored on secure encrypted servers. Biometric data is never shared with third parties without your consent."
